text: Abdelaziz Barrada (; 19 June 1989 – 24 October 2024), sometimes known as Abdel, was a French-born Moroccan professional footballer who played as a midfielder. He made 26 appearances for the Morocco national football team from 2012 to 2015. Barrada died of a heart attack in Paris, France on 24 October 2024, at the age of 35. ==References== ==Other websites== * Category:1989 births Category:2024 deaths Category:Footballers from Île-de-France Category:Moroccan footballers Category:People from Seine-et-Marne Category:Deaths from myocardial infarction
